## Instructions for Downloading and Running the Code

Follow the steps below to replicate the analysis on your local machine. This guide assumes you have a basic understanding of using Git and R.

### Prerequisites

1. **Install Git**
   - **Windows:** Download and install Git from [git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/download/win).
   - **macOS:** Install Git using Homebrew:
     ```bash
     brew install git
     ```
   - **Linux:** Install Git via your distributionâ€™s package manager, e.g.,
     ```bash
     sudo apt-get install git
     ```

2. **Install R**
   - Download and install R from [CRAN](https://cran.r-project.org/mirrors.html).

3. **Install RStudio (Optional but Recommended)**
   - Download and install RStudio from [rstudio.com](https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/).

### Step-by-Step Guide

#### 1. Clone the Repository

Open your terminal (or Git Bash on Windows) and execute the following command to clone the repository to your local machine:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/INF6027-project.git
